This paper deals with the algorithmic solution of parity games, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT). The algorithmic approach involves data structures and algorithms for graph traversal and manipulation, which are topics in data structures (cs.DS) and algorithms (cs.LO). The paper also discusses the derivation of winning strategies, which is a topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and programming languages (cs.PL).
